In a trilateral national security advisors meeting held in Tokyo, Japan on June 15, 2023, National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan, Japanese National Security Secretariat Secretary General Akiba Takeo, and ROK National Security Office Director Cho Tae-yong discussed various issues. They commended the efforts made by Seoul and Tokyo to strengthen bilateral ties and highlighted the potential of their trilateral partnership. The advisors addressed the illicit nuclear and missile programs of the DPRK and discussed ways to enhance coordination. They also discussed opportunities for cooperation in the East China Sea, South China Sea, and emphasized the importance of maintaining peace in the Taiwan Strait. Economic security cooperation, including critical technologies, energy security, and countering economic coercion, was also a topic of discussion. Mr. Sullivan reaffirmed the United States' commitment to the defense of Japan and the ROK, and the advisors talked about recent efforts to strengthen both alliances. They also expressed anticipation for an upcoming trilateral leaders' summit to be hosted by President Biden in the United States.